==English==

===Noun===
''Background Radiation'' is [[radiation]] that is naturally present in the environment.  If you turn on a detector such as a [[Geiger counter]] and are not near a source of radiation, the ambient activity reported by the detector is called the background radiation.  See [[w:Radiation#Natural_background_radiation|Wikipedia]] for more information.

